WEBVTT

00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:03.700
(September 13, 2025)

00:00:08.120 --> 00:00:09.950
Bro, this is awesome!

00:00:10.130 --> 00:00:13.390
I look pretty cool with my backpack, right?

00:00:13.750 --> 00:00:15.680
You look super cool.

00:00:16.410 --> 00:00:17.410
Oh, Manager!

00:00:17.470 --> 00:00:18.496
Manager, come take a photo with us!

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:20.430
Huh? Me too?

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:23.300
You want to take my picture?

00:00:29.570 --> 00:00:30.890
This is looking great.

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:32.160
Manager...

00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:34.450
Get a little closer to him.

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:35.860
Okay.

00:00:38.720 --> 00:00:39.600
- Dad.
- Yeah?

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:41.460
You need to fix your collar.

00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:43.060
Oh, thank you.

00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:46.280
Gakudo, you're such a good kid.

00:00:46.890 --> 00:00:50.069
Dad, I'm in the senior
class now. I'm a grown-up.

00:00:50.070 --> 00:00:52.020
Stop treating me like a baby.

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:55.140
Is that so?

00:00:55.940 --> 00:00:57.900
A real grown-up, huh?

00:00:58.300 --> 00:01:00.650
You've grown so much.

00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:04.320
Dad, stop playing around
and take the picture!

00:01:06.130 --> 00:01:08.570
Wataru, come join the photo.

00:01:09.380 --> 00:01:10.380
Are you sure?

00:01:10.460 --> 00:01:10.830
Yeah.

00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:13.570
Okay, let me just... set the timer.

00:01:14.030 --> 00:01:17.010
Alright. 9, 8, 7...

00:01:17.810 --> 00:01:19.990
6, 5, 4...

00:01:20.840 --> 00:01:22.450
3, 2...

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:24.290
1, 0!

00:01:30.470 --> 00:01:31.960
Nice, looks good.

00:01:32.490 --> 00:01:33.930
It turned out great, didn't it, Bro?

00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:35.620
Ah.

00:01:35.621 --> 00:01:36.820
Hey, Wataru.

00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:38.180
Look at this.

00:01:38.680 --> 00:01:39.680
Wow.

00:01:39.750 --> 00:01:40.859
That's a really good shot.

00:01:40.860 --> 00:01:41.860
Right?

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:46.650
Want me to show you how
to take even better ones?

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:51.180
Actually...

00:01:51.870 --> 00:01:54.130
There's a specific photo
I really want to take.

00:01:54.653 --> 00:01:55.653
A photo you want to take?

00:01:56.100 --> 00:01:57.100
Of the person I like.

00:01:57.580 --> 00:01:58.580
Someone you like?

00:01:58.650 --> 00:02:00.490
Yeah, from kindergarten.

00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:02.010
Ms. Megumi.

00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:05.330
Then just take it. Take a picture of her.

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:07.530
I can't, it's too embarrassing.

00:02:07.770 --> 00:02:08.630
If I take her picture...

00:02:08.631 --> 00:02:10.340
won't she find out that I like her?

00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:12.240
Find out you like her?

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:14.220
Dad always says...

00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:17.430
that photos are meant
to convey your feelings.

00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:20.970
Convey your feelings...

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:28.220
Dad gives a name to every photo he takes.

00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:29.680
It's so cool, right?

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:39.070
If I take a photo of Minato now...

00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:42.290
what kind of feelings
would the name of it reveal?

00:02:44.150 --> 00:02:45.150
Wataru?

00:02:48.930 --> 00:02:52.010
I... might be too scared to take it, too.

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:55.620
Wataru, is something bothering you?

00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:57.370
You can talk to me.

00:02:58.110 --> 00:02:59.270
Is it about someone you like?

00:03:00.340 --> 00:03:01.700
Do you have someone like that too?

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:05.030
Someone I like...

00:03:07.470 --> 00:03:09.670
Because I hate the idea of
being so far from you again.

00:03:13.530 --> 00:03:16.260
I... don't really know.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:09.000
"Countdown To Yes"

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:13.900
(July 14, 2019)

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:15.800
Yeah, just like that.

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:17.800
Lean back a little more.

00:04:17.850 --> 00:04:19.290
Try to blend in with the sunflowers.

00:04:20.710 --> 00:04:21.710
Blend in?

00:04:21.810 --> 00:04:22.810
Yeah.

00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:25.980
Right.

00:04:26.740 --> 00:04:27.740
A bit more.

00:04:28.830 --> 00:04:30.330
Perfect, perfect.

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:35.000
(Episode 3)

00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:36.330
Let me check. Hold on.

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:41.920
- Okay.
- How is it?

00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:43.130
Do I look good?

00:04:43.590 --> 00:04:46.259
Well... what do you think?

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:47.450
Hmm...

00:04:47.890 --> 00:04:49.619
I still prefer being shot from the left.

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:52.190
I'm more confident from that angle. See?

00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:54.929
When I took that photo
of Minato from this angle...

00:04:54.930 --> 00:04:56.500
it turned out pretty well.

00:04:58.910 --> 00:04:59.980
Maybe it's the lighting?

00:05:00.983 --> 00:05:03.803
You took such a great photo of Minato.

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:06.360
Can we try over there?

00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:08.930
I think I'd look better in that spot.

00:05:09.770 --> 00:05:10.770
Oh, uh...

00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:12.120
Sure, I guess.

00:05:18.600 --> 00:05:20.500
So this angle isn't it, huh?

00:05:24.990 --> 00:05:27.790
Wataru, let's take a break.

00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:29.800
Just a second.

00:05:36.760 --> 00:05:39.440
If I use this angle...

00:05:45.880 --> 00:05:48.729
Wataru, when it comes to photography...

00:05:48.730 --> 00:05:50.550
you get totally tunnel-visioned.

00:05:52.900 --> 00:05:55.250
I can put up with it because
you're my boyfriend...

00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:57.800
but if you were just
a friend, I'd be over it.

00:05:58.089 --> 00:06:00.169
What's that supposed to mean?
What are you saying?

00:06:00.531 --> 00:06:02.489
I mean, while I'm still
wearing "love goggles"...

00:06:02.490 --> 00:06:03.920
I can forgive you.

00:06:07.550 --> 00:06:08.550
Love goggles?

00:06:11.340 --> 00:06:12.340
Yeah.

00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:16.120
Let's take a break.

00:06:16.880 --> 00:06:17.880
Sorry, are you tired?

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:21.240
Next time, we'll go wherever
you want to take photos.

00:06:21.270 --> 00:06:22.930
Hmm... then I want to go to Hokkaido.

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:25.790
Hokkaido? That's a bit sudden.

00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:28.070
I've never been there before.

00:06:28.400 --> 00:06:29.400
Oh, I know.

00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:31.350
Let's go to Hokkaido for summer vacation.

00:06:32.910 --> 00:06:33.910
Oh...

00:06:34.430 --> 00:06:36.510
About Hokkaido...
I'm sorry.

00:06:36.910 --> 00:06:37.910
Why?

00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:40.590
I already promised Minato we'd go together.

00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:41.670
Minato again.

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:43.496
We're planning to travel across Hokkaido...

00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:44.880
and take as many photos as we can.

00:06:45.350 --> 00:06:47.110
We have to have Genghis
Khan BBQ, obviously.

00:06:47.230 --> 00:06:48.230
But wait...

00:06:48.231 --> 00:06:49.549
Eating that right after visiting a ranch...

00:06:49.550 --> 00:06:50.870
feels a little wrong, doesn't it?

00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:52.110
Must be nice.

00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:54.319
Fine, I'll just go with someone else.

00:06:54.506 --> 00:06:56.186
Oh! Maybe we'll run into each other there.

00:06:57.320 --> 00:06:58.880
We won't.

00:06:59.710 --> 00:07:01.636
Actually, we won't be seeing
each other at all anymore.

00:07:01.660 --> 00:07:02.000
Huh?

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.000
What do you mean?

00:07:05.510 --> 00:07:08.580
It was short, but I had fun.

00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:10.100
Bye.

00:07:32.380 --> 00:07:33.630
I'm home.

00:07:35.470 --> 00:07:36.470
Hey.

00:07:37.170 --> 00:07:38.170
Why do you look so down?

00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:39.960
Can you tell?

00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:41.670
I got dumped.

00:08:04.350 --> 00:08:05.350
What are you doing?

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:07.300
Celebrating your "getting
dumped" anniversary?

00:08:08.563 --> 00:08:10.403
Stop looking so happy
while taking my picture.

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:12.620
Ah...

00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:14.050
This is good.

00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:16.280
Tilt your head a bit more.

00:08:17.380 --> 00:08:18.380
Yeah.

00:08:21.810 --> 00:08:25.620
Is it really that bad to eat
Genghis Khan after the ranch?

00:08:27.893 --> 00:08:30.013
Would it be better if we
did it the other way around?

00:08:30.960 --> 00:08:33.660
It might be a little better that way.

00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:36.070
I figured.

00:08:38.710 --> 00:08:40.490
I'll never understand romance.

00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:44.450
It's so easy when we're just friends...

00:08:44.780 --> 00:08:47.410
but as soon as you're a
couple, it gets so complicated.

00:08:47.670 --> 00:08:48.670
Why is that?

00:08:50.310 --> 00:08:51.310
Who knows.

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:53.660
Whatever.

00:08:54.210 --> 00:08:57.570
Being with you is the
easiest and most fun anyway.

00:09:03.670 --> 00:09:04.670
Yeah.

00:09:04.770 --> 00:09:06.170
These bean sprouts are great today.

00:09:08.510 --> 00:09:10.250
I bought a new seasoning.

00:09:10.990 --> 00:09:11.990
Chili powder.

00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:16.710
That explains the kick.

00:09:18.530 --> 00:09:19.590
Got a problem with that?

00:09:20.640 --> 00:09:21.640
A problem?

00:09:21.880 --> 00:09:22.880
It's delicious.

00:09:23.860 --> 00:09:24.860
Good.

00:09:24.885 --> 00:09:25.885
Oh, right.

00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:28.070
About Hokkaido...

00:09:28.670 --> 00:09:29.870
Is a 5 AM start okay with you?

00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:36.550
(August 6, 2019)

00:09:36.550 --> 00:09:37.550
The Great...

00:09:37.820 --> 00:09:39.360
North.

00:10:09.990 --> 00:10:11.990
The usual cliché.

00:10:18.860 --> 00:10:20.690
Let me show you how to milk a cow.

00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:23.030
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:26.100
Got it?

00:10:26.810 --> 00:10:27.830
Yeah.

00:10:28.730 --> 00:10:29.730
Minato.

00:10:31.730 --> 00:10:32.730
- Wataru.
- Yeah?

00:10:33.270 --> 00:10:34.270
Look over here.

00:10:41.420 --> 00:10:42.420
Smile.

00:10:42.670 --> 00:10:43.670
I heard this is fresh.

00:10:44.150 --> 00:10:45.150
Thanks.

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:49.870
It's unsweetened.

00:10:50.010 --> 00:10:51.050
Can you handle it, Wataru?

00:10:53.640 --> 00:10:54.640
Oh.

00:10:55.140 --> 00:10:56.490
This yogurt is amazing.

00:10:57.260 --> 00:10:59.300
It's so sweet even without sugar. How?

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:00.640
You're exaggerating.

00:11:00.640 --> 00:11:01.640
No, really.

00:11:08.320 --> 00:11:09.320
It's good.

00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:10.520
Right?

00:11:20.340 --> 00:11:22.530
Must be the quality of the milk.

00:11:23.470 --> 00:11:24.470
What?

00:11:25.509 --> 00:11:27.180
You're like a yogurt expert now.

00:11:28.310 --> 00:11:29.339
Wataru, you've got some on your face.

00:11:29.340 --> 00:11:30.340
Huh?

00:11:31.530 --> 00:11:32.670
Not there, a bit higher.

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:34.460
Here?

00:11:34.730 --> 00:11:35.840
No, here.

00:11:39.860 --> 00:11:40.860
Did I get it?

00:11:42.590 --> 00:11:43.590
Yeah.

00:11:54.770 --> 00:11:58.030
Don't waste the film on me.

00:11:58.480 --> 00:11:59.570
I'm almost out anyway.

00:12:03.620 --> 00:12:05.170
Since we took so many...

00:12:05.450 --> 00:12:07.250
why don't we have a
private photo exhibition?

00:12:07.280 --> 00:12:08.280
Just for the two of us?

00:12:08.320 --> 00:12:09.320
Yeah.

00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:12.160
We can decorate the room with these photos.

00:12:12.520 --> 00:12:13.760
And we'll be the only audience.

00:12:16.600 --> 00:12:17.050
What? You don't want to?

00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:17.690
I do.

00:12:17.990 --> 00:12:18.990
Ah.

00:12:19.100 --> 00:12:21.170
Then we'd better take a lot more.

00:12:26.920 --> 00:12:28.160
Minato, hurry up!

00:12:30.570 --> 00:12:31.570
Wait for me.

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.200
What's with that face?

00:12:46.380 --> 00:12:47.380
Hello.

00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:49.080
Excuse us.

00:12:52.140 --> 00:12:53.140
Don't be scared.

00:12:53.250 --> 00:12:54.250
Welcome.

00:12:54.410 --> 00:12:55.700
Wataru.

00:12:58.610 --> 00:12:59.610
Minato.

00:13:08.050 --> 00:13:09.380
Are you going to take it?

00:13:10.156 --> 00:13:11.156
Wataru, you're shaking.

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:12.260
I am not.

00:13:12.650 --> 00:13:13.650
You totally are.

00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:23.720
Minato, you're really good at making these.

00:13:25.020 --> 00:13:26.830
Wataru, your fox is...

00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:32.510
unique.

00:13:32.790 --> 00:13:35.290
That's the point. It's more relatable.

00:13:37.830 --> 00:13:39.690
It kind of looks like you. It's cute.

00:13:40.390 --> 00:13:41.490
Really?

00:13:43.470 --> 00:13:44.910
I look like this?

00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:54.250
Oh!

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:55.400
(Photo exhibition for just the two of us)
Cows.

00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:57.440
- Moo.
- Moo.

00:13:57.730 --> 00:13:58.730
Oh, sheep!

00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:00.270
Whoa.

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:02.440
It's all... butts.

00:14:02.970 --> 00:14:04.160
Just a bunch of butts?

00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:08.790
- So many butts.
- Look at all those butts.

00:14:10.900 --> 00:14:11.900
Hey.

00:14:11.970 --> 00:14:12.970
This is a great photo.

00:14:14.070 --> 00:14:15.150
The composition is perfect.

00:14:16.380 --> 00:14:18.220
And the one of you
milking the cow in Otaru...

00:14:19.070 --> 00:14:20.070
is really well done.

00:14:21.350 --> 00:14:22.960
Yeah, it's a great shot.

00:14:30.530 --> 00:14:34.080
Did I... really look that
dorky feeding the sheep?

00:14:35.030 --> 00:14:36.920
Super dorky.

00:14:37.150 --> 00:14:38.270
Why didn't you say anything?

00:14:38.570 --> 00:14:39.570
It's a masterpiece.

00:14:40.220 --> 00:14:41.220
Ugh.

00:14:41.600 --> 00:14:42.600
Oh.

00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:43.870
This one's out of focus.

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:46.440
That's okay. It looks good that way.

00:14:47.390 --> 00:14:49.230
You mean it has "character"?

00:14:49.640 --> 00:14:50.640
Exactly.

00:14:52.370 --> 00:14:52.900
Oh.

00:14:53.210 --> 00:14:53.600
Hmm?

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:55.000
The birth of the calf.

00:14:55.680 --> 00:14:57.259
This photo is incredible.

00:14:57.260 --> 00:14:58.420
It's truly a beautiful photo.

00:15:00.010 --> 00:15:01.010
Oh, stop.

00:15:01.430 --> 00:15:03.340
No, it really is.

00:15:03.850 --> 00:15:05.450
Well, thanks. I'm glad you like it.

00:15:05.620 --> 00:15:06.910
Thank you.

00:15:07.030 --> 00:15:08.270
Thanks.

00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:21.400
(Hokkaido Yogurt:
Ultimate Concentration Challenge Project)

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.080
Good job today.

00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:26.840
Good job.

00:15:27.210 --> 00:15:28.210
I'll leave this to you.

00:15:28.860 --> 00:15:29.860
Yokoi.

00:15:30.530 --> 00:15:32.076
Make sure to increase the concentration.

00:15:32.100 --> 00:15:34.160
Got it.

00:15:37.740 --> 00:15:39.190
Hokkaido...

00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:47.100
(September 13, 2025)

00:15:54.420 --> 00:15:55.440
What's up?

00:15:55.970 --> 00:15:57.730
Why are you spacing out?

00:15:59.723 --> 00:16:01.383
Are you tired?

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:05.250
Yeah.

00:16:05.610 --> 00:16:06.980
I think I've hit a wall.

00:16:09.420 --> 00:16:10.420
I feel like...

00:16:11.180 --> 00:16:13.140
I can't take photos like I used to.

00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:14.990
Hmm?

00:16:15.303 --> 00:16:16.583
You mean your style?

00:16:18.320 --> 00:16:19.320
I guess.

00:16:19.470 --> 00:16:20.660
Something like that.

00:16:22.830 --> 00:16:23.830
I see.

00:16:24.890 --> 00:16:26.060
A slump, huh?

00:16:27.430 --> 00:16:28.430
But...

00:16:29.240 --> 00:16:31.240
it doesn't have to be
"like it used to be," right?

00:16:32.550 --> 00:16:35.340
But that's what I want.

00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:38.240
Just like before...

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:41.130
That was the best, the
happiest time for me.

00:16:43.820 --> 00:16:44.820
Is that so?

00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:49.670
Staying the same forever...

00:16:50.160 --> 00:16:51.160
Is that impossible?

00:16:51.860 --> 00:16:52.860
Well...

00:16:54.960 --> 00:16:58.150
People always tell me my style has changed.

00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:01.930
So I'm not really the one to ask.

00:17:05.130 --> 00:17:07.870
It's because I'm scared.

00:17:17.753 --> 00:17:20.329
(Minato: Let's take a walk)

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:34.960
It's been a while since
I've waited for you like this.

00:17:35.800 --> 00:17:38.600
(October 21, 2021)

00:17:38.680 --> 00:17:41.870
Next up, let's look at a submission
from "Eldest Son's Breeze."

00:17:42.920 --> 00:17:43.920
Wataru.

00:17:46.570 --> 00:17:47.570
Sorry.

00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:49.560
Developing the photos
took longer than I thought.

00:17:50.410 --> 00:17:53.500
They just mentioned "Postcard
King, Eldest Son's Breeze."

00:17:54.450 --> 00:17:55.450
And now...

00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:02.180
First up...

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:05.800
is...

00:18:06.750 --> 00:18:07.750
Everyone...

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:11.220
Sorry, Wataru.

00:18:12.810 --> 00:18:13.980
Overtime ran long.

00:18:15.970 --> 00:18:16.970
Overtime, huh?

00:18:17.770 --> 00:18:18.770
Hmm?

00:18:18.800 --> 00:18:19.800
What's wrong?

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:22.800
Nothing.

00:18:23.120 --> 00:18:24.880
Just thinking you've
really become an adult.

00:18:32.640 --> 00:18:33.640
Huh?

00:18:34.730 --> 00:18:35.810
No listening?

00:18:37.690 --> 00:18:38.690
Oh...

00:18:39.460 --> 00:18:40.460
Sure.

00:18:49.650 --> 00:18:50.650
Minato.

00:18:50.820 --> 00:18:52.900
It's been a while since
you listened to this, right?

00:18:53.180 --> 00:18:54.380
I've been listening all along.

00:18:54.736 --> 00:18:55.116
Really?

00:18:55.351 --> 00:18:57.280
Even when I was in Hokkaido.

00:18:58.740 --> 00:18:59.970
I'm a loyal listener.

00:19:12.300 --> 00:19:13.300
I can't.

00:19:14.090 --> 00:19:15.090
Huh?

00:19:15.680 --> 00:19:16.680
What?

00:19:17.310 --> 00:19:18.310
Oh.

00:19:18.370 --> 00:19:19.770
Nothing, it's nothing.

00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:23.070
I can't fall for him.

00:19:29.080 --> 00:19:32.050
Watch out, there's a bike coming.

00:19:39.210 --> 00:19:40.560
Back in college...

00:19:41.210 --> 00:19:43.850
didn't we use to walk
home like this all the time?

00:19:51.840 --> 00:19:52.840
Yeah.

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:55.660
Wataru, you're buying the juice.

00:19:56.450 --> 00:19:57.729
Why is it that since high school...

00:19:57.730 --> 00:19:58.890
I'm always the one paying?

00:19:59.330 --> 00:20:00.820
Because you always fall off.

00:20:01.630 --> 00:20:02.630
One more time.

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:07.320
Don't fall off this time.

00:20:22.850 --> 00:20:23.850
No, no, no! Ah!

00:20:24.110 --> 00:20:25.110
Hey!

00:20:39.810 --> 00:20:40.280
Wataru.

00:20:40.930 --> 00:20:41.930
What?

00:20:42.470 --> 00:20:43.499
We should really just live together.

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:44.180
No.

00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:45.180
That was fast.

00:20:45.940 --> 00:20:47.450
I'm not living with you again.

00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:49.119
Why not?

00:20:49.120 --> 00:20:50.120
Just because.

00:20:51.140 --> 00:20:54.980
Didn't you have fun today...
walking together like we used to?

00:20:55.700 --> 00:20:57.050
Just like in college.

00:20:57.330 --> 00:20:59.090
I want to eat your burnt
bean sprouts again.

00:20:59.730 --> 00:21:01.320
I'm an adult now.

00:21:01.570 --> 00:21:02.740
I don't do that anymore.

00:21:03.050 --> 00:21:04.130
Then as an adult, Wataru...

00:21:05.220 --> 00:21:06.220
let's live together.

00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:08.590
How does it even lead to that?

00:21:08.850 --> 00:21:10.450
I just want it to be like college again.

00:21:10.550 --> 00:21:11.940
Stop talking about college.

00:21:12.293 --> 00:21:14.853
You were the first one to leave
our student days behind, Minato.

00:21:17.210 --> 00:21:18.210
Wataru, are you mad?

00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:20.270
Because you gave up photography...

00:21:22.860 --> 00:21:24.679
and joined a company
that has nothing to do with it.

00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:25.720
Then you just disappeared.

00:21:26.480 --> 00:21:27.569
And now you suddenly show up...

00:21:27.570 --> 00:21:28.800
and ask to move in?

00:21:30.740 --> 00:21:32.230
I didn't give up on photography.

00:21:34.243 --> 00:21:36.283
My way of doing it might
be different from yours...

00:21:36.690 --> 00:21:37.710
but I still cherish it.

00:21:37.820 --> 00:21:38.820
I know.

00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:53.120
Wataru?

00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:56.230
Sorry.

00:21:56.840 --> 00:21:57.870
I'm not mad at you.

00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:00.120
I'm mad at myself.

00:22:02.310 --> 00:22:03.310
Why?

00:22:04.700 --> 00:22:05.850
Because after you left...

00:22:06.210 --> 00:22:07.670
I wouldn't admit how lonely I was.

00:22:09.370 --> 00:22:11.050
I'm mad at myself for being such an idiot.

00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:18.230
What's with that face?

00:22:22.380 --> 00:22:23.380
Me too.

00:22:24.600 --> 00:22:25.560
After we were apart...

00:22:25.561 --> 00:22:27.310
I realized how much that time meant to me.

00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:31.080
If you feel the same way, Wataru...

00:22:31.080 --> 00:22:32.080
then let's start over.

00:22:34.570 --> 00:22:35.570
I...

00:22:35.770 --> 00:22:37.410
don't really have a reason to leave home.

00:22:37.570 --> 00:22:39.160
You could eat with me every day.

00:22:39.570 --> 00:22:40.350
I can't afford rent.

00:22:40.351 --> 00:22:41.779
You don't have to pay.
Let's just live together.

00:22:41.780 --> 00:22:43.249
If we're living together,
of course I'm paying rent.

00:22:43.250 --> 00:22:44.586
Fine, then pay rent
and let's live together.

00:22:44.610 --> 00:22:47.420
Look... the answer is just no.

00:22:50.120 --> 00:22:51.180
But why?

00:22:51.629 --> 00:22:52.859
Because I'm in love with you.

00:23:00.110 --> 00:23:01.110
(Next Episode)
Wait!

00:23:01.230 --> 00:23:01.700
Time out!

00:23:02.213 --> 00:23:05.063
Isn't a one-of-a-kind best friend
more important than a lover?

00:23:05.320 --> 00:23:06.789
I feel like that's something
we wouldn't understand.

00:23:06.790 --> 00:23:08.430
A time that belongs only to them.

00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:10.410
Just like we used to have.

00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:12.700
What Minato and I had "back then"...

00:23:13.070 --> 00:23:14.070
what was it really like?